WEBVTT

00:27.080 --> 00:29.840
CHAPTER XXXII.

00:30.240 --> 00:35.420
And Jacob went on his way, and the angels of God met him. And when Jacob saw them,

00:35.420 --> 00:42.160
he said, This is God's host, and he called the name of that place Mayoneum. And Jacob

00:42.160 --> 00:47.920
sent messengers before him to Esau his brother unto the land of Seir, the country of Edom.

00:48.460 --> 00:54.540
And he commanded them, saying, Thus shall ye speak unto my lord Esau. Thy servant Jacob

00:54.540 --> 01:00.960
saith thus, I have sojourned with Laban, and stayed there until now. And I have oxen and

01:00.960 --> 01:07.040
asses, flocks, and men's servants, and women's servants. And I have sent to tell my lord

01:07.040 --> 01:13.700
that I may find grace in thy sight. And the messengers returned to Jacob, saying, We came

01:13.700 --> 01:23.680
to thy brother Esau, and also he cometh to meet thee and four hundred men with him. Then

01:23.680 --> 01:28.860
the people that was with him, and the flocks and herds, and the camels, into two bands.

01:29.480 --> 01:34.800
And said, If Esau come to the one company, and smite it, then the other company which

01:34.800 --> 01:42.000
is left shall escape. And Jacob said, O God of my father Abraham, and God of my father

01:42.000 --> 01:48.360
Isaac, the Lord which said unto me, Return unto thy country, and to thy kindred, and

01:49.040 --> 01:55.080
with thee. I am not worthy of the least of all the mercies and of all the truth which

01:55.080 --> 02:01.060
thou hast shewed unto thy servant, for with my staff I passed over this Jordan, and now

02:01.060 --> 02:07.200
I am become two bands. Deliver me, I pray thee, from the hand of my brother, from the

02:07.200 --> 02:12.640
hand of Esau, for I fear him lest he will come and smite me, and the mother with the

02:12.640 --> 02:18.640
children. And thou saidest, I will surely do thee good, and make thy seed as the sand

02:18.640 --> 02:25.420
of the sea, which cannot be numbered for multitude. And he lodged there that same night, and took

02:25.420 --> 02:31.400
of that which came to his hand a present for Esau his brother. Two hundred she-goats, and

02:31.400 --> 02:37.080
twenty he-goats, two hundred ewes, and twenty rams, thirty milk-camels with their colts,

02:37.080 --> 02:44.300
forty kine, and ten bulls, twenty she-asses, and ten foals. And he delivered them into

02:44.300 --> 02:50.480
the hand of his servants, every drove by themselves, and said unto his servants, Pass over before

02:50.480 --> 02:56.760
me, and put a space betwixt drove and grove. And he commanded the foremost, saying, When

02:56.760 --> 03:02.920
Esau my brother meeteth thee, and asketh thee, saying, Whos art thou, and whither goest thou,

03:02.920 --> 03:09.760
and whos are these before thee? Then thou shalt say, They be thy servant Jacob's, it

03:09.760 --> 03:16.600
is a present sent unto my lord Esau, and behold also he is behind us. And so commanded he

03:16.600 --> 03:22.140
the second, and the third, and all that followed the droves, saying, On this manner shall ye

03:22.140 --> 03:28.960
speak unto Esau when ye find him. And say ye moreover, Behold, thy servant Jacob is

03:28.960 --> 03:34.380
behind us. For he said, I will appease him with the present that goeth before me, and

03:34.380 --> 03:40.940
afterward I will see his face. Peradventure he will accept of me. So went the present

03:40.940 --> 03:47.000
over before him, and himself lodged that night in the company. And he rose up that night,

03:47.120 --> 03:52.540
and took his two wives, and his two women's servants, and his eleven sons, and passed

03:52.540 --> 03:58.060
over the ford Jabbok. And he took them, and sent them over the brook, and sent over that

03:58.060 --> 04:03.720
he had. And Jacob was left alone, and there wrestled a man with him until the breaking

04:03.720 --> 04:09.500
of the day. And when he saw that he prevailed not against him, he touched the hollow of

04:09.500 --> 04:14.820
his thigh, and the hollow of Jacob's thigh was out of joint as he wrestled with him.

04:15.180 --> 04:21.920
And he said, Let me go, for the day breaketh. And he said, I will not let thee go, except

04:22.280 --> 04:30.340
me. And he said unto him, What is thy name? And he said, Jacob. And he said, Thy name

04:30.340 --> 04:36.840
shall be called no more Jacob, but Israel, for as a prince hast thou power with God and

04:36.840 --> 04:44.320
with men, and hast prevailed. And Jacob asked him, and said, Tell me, I pray thee, thy name.

04:44.700 --> 04:50.640
And he said, Wherefore is it that thou dost ask after my name? And he blessed him there.

04:52.060 --> 04:58.660
And Jacob called the name of the place Peniel, for I have seen God face to face, and my life

04:58.660 --> 05:05.800
is preserved. And as he passed over Penuel, the sun rose upon him, and he halted upon

05:05.800 --> 05:12.460
his thigh. Therefore the children of Israel eat not of the sinew which shrank, which is

05:12.460 --> 05:17.740
upon the hollow of the thigh unto this day, because he touched the hollow of Jacob's thigh

05:17.740 --> 05:20.320
in the sinew that shrank.

05:20.940 --> 05:22.060
CHAPTER XXXIII

05:22.860 --> 05:29.140
And Jacob lifted up his eyes, and looked, and behold Esau came, and with him four hundred

05:29.140 --> 05:35.160
men. And he divided the children unto Leah, and unto Rachel, and unto the two handmaids.

05:36.000 --> 05:41.060
Then he put the handmaids and their children foremost, and Leah and her children after,

05:41.060 --> 05:47.900
and Rachel and Joseph hindermost. And he passed over before them, and bowed himself to the

05:47.900 --> 05:54.580
ground seven times, until he came near to his brother. And Esau ran to meet him, and

05:54.580 --> 06:00.600
embraced him, and fell on his neck, and kissed him, and they wept. And he lifted up his eyes,

06:00.680 --> 06:06.440
and saw the women and the children, and said, Who are those with thee? and he said, The

06:06.440 --> 06:12.960
children which God hath graciously given that I servant. Then the handmaids came near, they

06:12.960 --> 06:18.540
and their children, and they bowed themselves. And Leah also with her children came near,

06:18.820 --> 06:24.220
and bowed themselves, and after came Joseph near, and Rachel, and they bowed themselves.

06:24.920 --> 06:30.880
And he said, What meanest thou by all this drove which I met? and he said, These are

06:30.880 --> 06:37.540
find grace in the sight of my Lord. And Esau said, I have enough, my brother, keep that

06:37.540 --> 06:44.780
thou hast unto thyself. And Jacob said, Nay, I pray thee, if now I have found grace in

06:44.780 --> 06:51.160
thy sight, then receive my present at my hand, for therefore I have seen thy face as though

06:51.160 --> 06:57.380
I had seen the face of God, and thou wast pleased with me. Take, I pray thee, my blessing

06:57.380 --> 07:02.540
that is brought to thee, because God hath dealt graciously with me, and because I have

07:02.540 --> 07:09.180
enough. And he urged him, and he took it. And he said, Let us take our journey, and

07:09.180 --> 07:15.020
let us go, and I will go before thee. And he said unto him, My Lord knoweth that the

07:15.020 --> 07:19.960
children are tender, and the flocks and herds with young are with me, and if men should

07:19.960 --> 07:26.360
overdrive them one day, all the flock will die. Let my Lord, I pray thee, pass over before

07:26.360 --> 07:32.220
his servant, and I will lead on softly, according as the cattle that goeth before me, and the

07:32.220 --> 07:39.300
children be able to endure, until I come unto my Lord, unto Seir. And Esau said, Let me

07:39.300 --> 07:44.360
now leave with thee some of the folk that are with me. And he said, What needeth it,

07:44.540 --> 07:50.640
let me find grace in the sight of my Lord. So Esau returned that day on his way unto

07:50.640 --> 07:56.800
Seir. And Jacob journeyed to Succoth, and built him in house, and made boots for his

07:56.800 --> 08:02.960
cattle. Therefore the name of the place is called Succoth. And Jacob came to Shalem,

08:03.120 --> 08:08.320
a city of Shechem, which is in the land of Canaan, when he came from Payton Aram, and

08:08.320 --> 08:14.090
pitched his tent before the city. And he bought a parcel of a field where he had spread his

08:14.090 --> 08:19.210
tent, at the hand of the children of Hamor, Shechem's father, for an hundred pieces of

08:19.210 --> 08:24.970
money. And he erected there an altar, and called it El Elohi Israel.

08:27.170 --> 08:31.170
CHAPTER XXXIV And Dinah, the daughter of Leah, which she

08:31.170 --> 08:36.990
bare unto Jacob, went out to see the daughters of the land. And when Shechem, the son of

08:36.990 --> 08:43.190
Hamor the Hivite, prince of the country, saw her, he took her, and lay with her, and defiled

08:43.190 --> 08:49.690
her. And his soul clave unto Dinah, the daughter of Jacob, and he loved the damsel, and spake

08:49.690 --> 08:56.110
kindly unto the damsel. And Shechem spake unto his father Hamor, saying, Get me this

08:56.110 --> 09:02.430
damsel to wife. And Jacob heard that he had defiled Dinah, his daughter, that his sons

09:02.430 --> 09:08.730
were with his cattle in the field, and Jacob held his peace until they were come. And Hamor,

09:08.730 --> 09:13.970
the father of Shechem, went out unto Jacob to commune with him. And the sons of Jacob

09:13.970 --> 09:18.430
came out of the field when they heard it, and the men were grieved, and they were very

09:18.430 --> 09:23.570
wroth because he had wrought folly in Israel in lying with Jacob's daughter, which thing

09:23.570 --> 09:30.310
ought not to be done. And Hamor communed with them, saying, The soul of my son Shechem longeth

09:30.310 --> 09:36.350
for your daughter. I pray you give her him to wife. And make ye marriages with us, and

09:36.350 --> 09:41.150
give your daughters unto us, and take our daughters unto you. And ye shall dwell with

09:41.150 --> 09:46.710
us, and the land shall be before you. Dwell and trade ye therein, and get you possessions

09:46.710 --> 09:53.030
therein. And Shechem said unto her father, and unto her brethren, Let me find grace in

09:53.030 --> 09:58.990
your eyes, and what ye shall say unto me, I will give. Ask me never so much dowry and

09:58.990 --> 10:04.510
gift, and I will give according as ye shall say unto me. But give me the damsel to wife.

10:05.470 --> 10:11.350
And the sons of Jacob answered Shechem and Hamor his father deceitfully, and said, Because

10:11.350 --> 10:16.530
he had defiled Dinah their sister. And they said unto them, We cannot do this thing to

10:16.530 --> 10:22.970
give our sister to one that is uncircumcised, for that were a reproach unto us. But in this

10:22.970 --> 10:28.410
will we consent unto you, if ye will be as we be, that every male of you be circumcised.

10:28.750 --> 10:33.570
Then will we give our daughters unto you, and we will take your daughters to us, and

10:33.570 --> 10:38.870
we will dwell with you, and we will become one people. But if ye will not hearken unto

10:38.870 --> 10:45.210
us to be circumcised, then will we take our daughter, and we will be gone. And their words

10:45.210 --> 10:51.090
pleased Hamor and Shechem Hamor's son. And the young man deferred not to do the thing,

10:51.150 --> 10:56.010
because he had delight in Jacob's daughter, and he was more honorable than all the house

10:56.010 --> 11:02.250
of his father. And Hamor and Shechem his son came unto the gate of their city, and communed

11:02.250 --> 11:07.250
with the men of their city, saying, These men are peaceable with us, therefore let them

11:07.250 --> 11:12.610
dwell in the land and trade therein. For the land, behold, it is large enough for them.

11:13.030 --> 11:19.210
Let us take their daughters to us for wives, and let us give them our daughters. Only herein

11:19.210 --> 11:24.630
will the men consent unto us, for to dwell with us, to be one people, if every male among

11:24.630 --> 11:30.430
us be circumcised as they are circumcised. Shall not their cattle and their substance

11:30.430 --> 11:35.450
and every beast of theirs be ours? Only let us consent unto them, and they will dwell

11:35.450 --> 11:41.250
with us. And unto Hamor and unto Shechem his son hearkened all that went out of the gate

11:41.250 --> 11:46.650
of his city, and every male was circumcised all that went out of the gate of his city.

11:47.770 --> 11:52.810
And it came to pass on the third day, when they were sore, that two of the sons of Jacob,

11:53.150 --> 11:58.970
Simeon and Levi, Dinah's brethren, took each man his sword, and came upon the city boldly,

11:58.970 --> 12:04.830
and slew all the males. And they slew Hamor and Shechem his son with the edge of the sword,

12:05.170 --> 12:11.050
and took Dinah out of Shechem's house, and went out. The sons of Jacob came upon the

12:11.050 --> 12:16.890
slain and spoiled the city, because they had defiled their sister. They took their sheep,

12:17.050 --> 12:21.490
and their oxen, and their asses, and that which was in the city, and that which was

12:21.490 --> 12:25.990
in the field, and all their wealth, and all their little ones, and their wives took they

12:25.990 --> 12:29.290
captive, and spoiled even all that was in the house.

12:30.530 --> 12:32.590
And Jacob said to Simeon and Levi,

12:32.950 --> 12:38.250
E have troubled me to make me to stink among the inhabitants of the land, among the Canaanites

12:38.250 --> 12:43.530
and the Perizzites, and I, being few in number, they shall gather themselves together against

12:43.530 --> 12:47.850
me and slay me, and I shall be destroyed, I and my house.

12:48.450 --> 12:49.390
And they said,

12:49.710 --> 12:52.710
Should he deal with our sister as with an harlot?

12:54.510 --> 12:55.550
CHAPTER 35

12:56.190 --> 12:57.970
And God said unto Jacob,

12:58.350 --> 13:03.870
Arise, go up to Bethel, and dwell there, and make there an altar unto God, that appeared

13:03.870 --> 13:07.170
unto thee when thou fledtest from the face of Esau thy brother.

13:08.110 --> 13:11.890
Then Jacob said unto his household, and to all that were with him,

13:12.150 --> 13:17.830
Put away the strange gods that are among you, and be clean, and change your garments. And

13:17.830 --> 13:23.910
go up to Bethel, and I will make there an altar unto God, who answered me in the day

13:23.910 --> 13:27.390
of my distress, and was with me in the way which I went.

13:28.330 --> 13:33.570
And they gave unto Jacob all the strange gods which were in their hand, and all their earrings

13:33.570 --> 13:38.210
which were in their ears, and Jacob hid them under the oak which was by Shechem.

13:39.390 --> 13:43.890
And they journeyed, and the terror of God was upon the cities that were round about

13:43.890 --> 13:47.010
them, and they did not pursue after the sons of Jacob.

13:48.070 --> 13:53.550
So Jacob came to Luz, which is in the land of Canaan, that is, Bethel, he and all the

13:53.550 --> 13:58.930
people that were with him. And he built there an altar, and called the place El-Bethel,

13:59.190 --> 14:03.190
because there God appeared unto him when he fled from the face of his brother.

14:04.110 --> 14:09.950
But Deborah, Rebecca's nurse, died, and she was buried beneath Bethel under an oak, and

14:09.950 --> 14:12.530
the name of it was called El-Anbaikoth.

14:13.570 --> 14:18.850
And God appeared unto Jacob again, when he came out of Paedon Aram, and blessed him.

14:19.310 --> 14:24.670
And God said unto him, Thy name is Jacob, thy name shall not be called any more Jacob,

14:24.990 --> 14:28.730
but Israel shall be thy name. And he called his name Israel.

14:29.750 --> 14:36.690
And God said unto him, I am God Almighty, be fruitful and multiply, a nation and a company

14:36.690 --> 14:42.330
of nations shall be of thee, and kings shall come out of thy loins. And the land which

14:42.330 --> 14:48.110
I give Abraham and Isaac to thee I will give it, and to thy seed after thee will I give

14:48.110 --> 14:48.770
the land.

14:49.910 --> 14:53.130
And God went up from him in the place where he talked with him.

14:54.090 --> 14:58.770
And Jacob set up a pillar in the place where he talked with him, even a pillar of stone,

14:59.090 --> 15:04.670
and he poured a drink offering thereon, and he poured oil thereon. And Jacob called the

15:04.670 --> 15:07.590
name of the place where God spake with him Bethel.

15:08.470 --> 15:13.350
And they journeyed from Bethel, and there was but a little way to come to Ephrath, and

15:13.350 --> 15:18.990
Rachel travailed, and she had hard labor. And it came to pass, when she was in hard

15:18.990 --> 15:25.910
labor, that the midwife said unto her, Fear not, thou shalt have this son also. And it

15:25.910 --> 15:31.730
came to pass, as her soul was in departing, for she died, that she called his name Ben-Onai,

15:31.730 --> 15:38.310
but his father called him Benjamin. And Rachel died, and was buried in the way to Ephrath,

15:38.450 --> 15:44.690
which is Bethlehem. And Jacob set a pillar upon her grave, that is the pillar of Rachel's

15:44.690 --> 15:46.170
grave unto this day.

15:47.970 --> 15:53.570
And Israel journeyed, and spread his tent beyond the tower of Edar. And it came to pass,

15:53.610 --> 15:58.990
when Israel dwelt in that land that Reuben went, and lay with Bilha his father's concubine,

15:58.990 --> 16:05.890
and Israel heard it. Now the sons of Jacob were twelve. The sons of Leah, Reuben, Jacob's

16:05.890 --> 16:12.570
first born, and Simeon, and Levi, and Judah, and Issachar, and Zebulun. The sons of Rachel,

16:12.830 --> 16:19.110
Joseph, and Benjamin. And the sons of Bilha, Rachel's handmaid, Dan, and Naphtali. And

16:19.110 --> 16:24.370
the sons of Zilpah, Leah's handmaid, Gad, and Asher. These were the sons of Jacob, which

16:24.370 --> 16:31.330
were born to him, and paid in Aram. And Jacob came unto Isaac his father, unto Mamre, unto

16:31.330 --> 16:37.950
the city of Arba, which is Hebron, where Abraham and Isaac sojourned. And the days of Isaac

16:37.950 --> 16:44.110
were a hundred and four score years. And Isaac gave up the ghost, and died, and was gathered

16:44.110 --> 16:50.610
unto his people, being old and full of days. And his sons Esau and Jacob buried him.

16:51.830 --> 16:56.310
CHAPTER XXXVI Now these are the generations of Esau, who

16:56.310 --> 17:02.950
is Edom. Esau took his wives of the daughters of Canaan, Adah the daughter of Elan the Hittite,

17:03.350 --> 17:09.190
and Ahol Abbaamah the daughter of Anah the daughter of Zibion the Hivite, and Bashamath

17:09.190 --> 17:17.230
Ishmael's daughter, sister of Nebejath. And Adah bare to Esau a life-faz, and Bashamath

17:17.230 --> 17:24.290
bare rule. And Ahol Abbaamah, Berjish, and Jalim, and Korah, these were the sons of Esau,

17:24.410 --> 17:29.950
which were born unto him in the land of Canaan. And Esau took his wives, and his sons, and

17:29.950 --> 17:34.650
his daughters, and all the persons of his house, and his cattle, and all his beasts,

17:34.750 --> 17:39.850
and all his substance, which he had got in the land of Canaan, and went into the country

17:39.850 --> 17:44.710
from the face of his brother Jacob. For their riches were more than that they might dwell

17:44.710 --> 17:49.410
together, and the land wherein they were strangers could not bear them because of their cattle.

17:50.550 --> 17:57.810
Thus Esau dwelt in Mount Seir. Esau is Edom. And these are the generations of Esau, the

17:57.810 --> 18:04.150
father of the Edomites in Mount Seir. These are the names of Esau's sons. Eliphaz, the

18:04.150 --> 18:11.050
son of Edah, the wife of Esau, rule, the son of Bashamath, the wife of Esau. And the sons

18:11.050 --> 18:19.070
of Eliphaz were Timon, Omar, Zepho, and Gatam, and Kenaz. And Timna was concubine to Eliphaz,

18:19.230 --> 18:25.490
Esau's son, and she bore to Eliphaz Amalek. These were the sons of Edah, Esau's wife.

18:26.530 --> 18:32.150
And these were the sons of Rul, Nahath, and Zirah, Shammah, and Mizzah. These were the

18:32.150 --> 18:38.290
sons of Bashamath, Esau's wife. And these were the sons of Ahalibamah, the daughter

18:38.290 --> 18:45.490
of Ana, the daughter of Zibian, Esau's wife. And she bore to Esau, Jeash, and Jalem, and

18:45.490 --> 18:52.050
Korah. These were the dukes of the sons of Esau, the sons of Eliphaz, the firstborn son

18:52.050 --> 19:00.030
of Esau, duke Timon, duke Omar, duke Zepho, duke Kenaz, duke Korah, duke Gatam, and duke

19:00.030 --> 19:05.770
Amalek. These are the dukes that came of Eliphaz in the land of Edom. These were the sons of

19:05.770 --> 19:13.530
Edah. And these were the sons of Rul, Esau's son, duke Nahath, duke Zirah, duke Shammah,

19:13.630 --> 19:18.790
duke Mizzah. These were the dukes that came of Rul in the land of Edom. These were the

19:18.790 --> 19:25.650
sons of Bashamath, Esau's wife. And these were the sons of Ahalibamah, Esau's wife,

19:26.150 --> 19:35.750
duke Jeash, duke Jalem, duke Korah. These were the dukes that came of Ahalibamah, the

19:35.750 --> 19:39.570
sons of Esau, who is Edom, and these are their dukes.

19:40.870 --> 19:47.390
These are the sons of Seir, the Horite, who inhabited the land, Lotan and Shobol and Zibian

19:47.390 --> 19:54.790
and Einah and Daishan and Ezer and Daishan. These are the dukes of the Horites, the children

19:54.790 --> 20:01.950
of Seir in the land of Edom. And the children of Lotan were Horai and Hemam, and Lotan's

20:01.950 --> 20:10.430
sister was Timna. And the children of Shobol were these, Alvin and Manahath and Ebel, Shifo

20:10.430 --> 20:17.750
and Onam. And these were the children of Zibian, both Aja and Einah. This was that Einah that

20:17.750 --> 20:24.090
found the mules in the wilderness as he fed the asses of Zibian his father. And the children

20:24.090 --> 20:30.030
of Einah were these, Daishan and Ahalibamah, the daughter of Einah. And these were the

20:30.030 --> 20:37.250
children of Daishan, Hemdan and Eshban and Ithran and Kiran. The children of Ezer are

20:37.250 --> 20:46.450
these, Bilhan and Zayavan and Akan. The children of Daishan are these, Uz and Aaron. These

20:46.450 --> 20:52.650
are the dukes that come of the Horites, duke Lotan, duke Shobol, duke Zibian, duke Einah,

20:52.850 --> 20:59.470
duke Daishan, duke Ezer, duke Daishan. These are the dukes that come of Horai, among their

20:59.470 --> 21:05.470
dukes in the land of Seir. And these are the kings that reigned in the land of Edom before

21:05.470 --> 21:11.270
there reigned any king over the children of Israel. And Bela, the son of Beor, reigned

21:11.270 --> 21:18.010
in Edom, and the name of his city was Dinhabah. And Bela died, and Jobab, the son of Zerah,

21:18.070 --> 21:25.050
of Basra, reigned in his stead. And Jobab died, and Husham, the land of Timani, reigned

21:25.050 --> 21:31.510
in his stead. And Husham died, and Hadad, the son of Beedad, who smote Midian in the

21:31.510 --> 21:38.490
field of Moab, reigned in his stead. And the name of his city was Avoth. And Hadad died,

21:38.750 --> 21:45.610
and Samlah, of Masrika, reigned in his stead. And Samlah died, and Saul, of Rehoboth, by

21:45.610 --> 21:52.250
the river, reigned in his stead. And Saul died, and Baal-Hanan, the son of Aqbor, reigned

21:52.250 --> 21:59.170
in his stead. And Baal-Hanan, the son of Aqbor, died, and Hadar reigned in his stead. And

21:59.170 --> 22:05.090
the name of his city was Peu, and his wife's name was Mehedabal, the daughter of Matred,

22:05.450 --> 22:11.510
the daughter of Mizahab. And these are the names of the dukes that came of Esau according

22:11.510 --> 22:18.510
to their families after their places by their names. Duke Timnah, Duke Alva, Duke Jetheth,

22:18.510 --> 22:27.030
